During Setup() It's instead saving the multiplied matrix 
 - Matrix.Multiply(ref _matrix, ref projection, out projection);
to the 
 - _matrixTransform.SetValue(projection);
that is a readonly and is never updated when a custom effect is added to the SB.Begin.
 - readonly EffectParameter _matrixTransform;

I'm not sure if this is an easy fix, or is instead very complex due to "not all Effects expose a "MatrixTransform" parameter. But the spritebatch should at least warn the user that the projection matrix must be set by hand and the one that is given to the Begin() method will be discarded.
Hope i was clear enough.
